    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This function uses a sequence of cubic Bézier curves to create an arc that is tangent to the line from the current point to (x1,y1) and to the line from (x1,y1) to (x2,y2). The start and end points of the arc are located on the first and second tangent lines, respectively. The start and end points of the arc are also the “tangent points” of the lines."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If the current point and the first tangent point of the arc (the starting point) are not equal, Core Graphics appends a straight line segment from the current point to the first tangent point."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The ending point of the arc becomes the new current point of the path."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For another way to draw an arc in a path, see "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/1411147-cgpathaddarc"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
